<subSubSection id="DF97549A9C17FFB8D0BBFD61FCFAFBC4" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="973207119C17FFB8D0BBFD61FCFAFBC4" blockId="7.[151,1437,761,2015]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D0BBFD61FEE4FCAC" box="[151,361,761,786]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D0BBFD61FEE4FCAC" box="[151,361,761,786]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<typeStatus id="4836B9B39C17FFB8D150FD61FE21FCAC" box="[380,428,762,786]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D296FD61FC5CFCAC" authority="Kieffer, 1894" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1894" box="[698,977,761,786]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D296FD61FCABFCAF" box="[698,806,762,785]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D31FFD62FC5CFCAC" author="Kieffer" box="[819,977,761,786]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Kieffer, J. - J. (1894) M. l'abbe J. - J. Kieffer adresse aussi une note preliminaire sur le genre Campylomyza (Dipt.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1894, clxxv - clxxvi." type="journal volume" year="1894">Kieffer, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was previously known only from the incomplete descriptions by 
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D1E3FC86FDF9FC88" author="Kieffer" box="[463,628,797,822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Kieffer, J. - J. (1894) M. l'abbe J. - J. Kieffer adresse aussi une note preliminaire sur le genre Campylomyza (Dipt.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1894, clxxv - clxxvi." type="journal volume" year="1894">Kieffer (1894)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D2AEFC86FCB5FC88" author="Edwards" box="[642,824,797,822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1938) On the British Lestremiinae, with notes on exotic species. 7. (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 7, 253 - 265." type="journal article" year="1938">Edwards (1938)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D35AFC86FBB6FC88" author="Kleesattel" box="[886,1083,797,822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Kleesattel, W. (1979) Beitrage zu einer Revision der Lestremiinae (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) unter besonderer Berucksichtigung ihrer Phylogenie. University of Stuttgart Dissertation, Stuttgart, 203 pp." type="book" year="1979">Kleesattel (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, all based on Kieffer’s original material collected in 
<collectingCountry id="EF9A47819C17FFB8D1AAFCD9FE5FFCE7" box="[390,466,834,857]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">France</collectingCountry>
in 1893. 
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D213FCDAFD6FFCE4" author="Kieffer" box="[575,738,833,858]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Kieffer, J. - J. (1894) M. l'abbe J. - J. Kieffer adresse aussi une note preliminaire sur le genre Campylomyza (Dipt.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1894, clxxv - clxxvi." type="journal volume" year="1894">Kieffer (1894)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D3ABFCD9FC7EFCE7" box="[903,1011,834,857]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D3ABFCD9FC7EFCE7" box="[903,1011,834,857]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D415FCD9FB2BFCE7" box="[1081,1190,834,857]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Joannisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D415FCD9FB2BFCE7" box="[1081,1190,834,857]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Joannisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus described in the same paper, chiefly by the number of palpal segments, two in 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D35FFCFDFC52FCC3" box="[883,991,870,893]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D35FFCFDFC52FCC3" box="[883,991,870,893]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and four in 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D44AFCFDFB5EFCC3" box="[1126,1235,870,893]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Joannisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D44AFCFDFB5EFCC3" box="[1126,1235,870,893]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Joannisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As this character cannot suffice for separating otherwise similar genera, synonymization of the two names was suggested by 
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D0BBFC36FEC3FC78" author="Edwards" box="[151,334,941,966]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1938) On the British Lestremiinae, with notes on exotic species. 7. (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 7, 253 - 265." type="journal article" year="1938">Edwards (1938)</bibRefCitation>
and put into effect by 
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D24DFC36FCA4FC78" author="Kleesattel" box="[609,809,941,966]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Kleesattel, W. (1979) Beitrage zu einer Revision der Lestremiinae (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) unter besonderer Berucksichtigung ihrer Phylogenie. University of Stuttgart Dissertation, Stuttgart, 203 pp." type="book" year="1979">Kleesattel (1979)</bibRefCitation>
. Of 160 species known of 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D446FC35FB5BFC7B" box="[1130,1238,942,965]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D446FC35FB5BFC7B" box="[1130,1238,942,965]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
today (
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D51DFC35FEB3FC54" author="Gagne" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Gagne, R. J. &amp; Jaschhof, M. (2014) A Catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the World. 3 rd Edition. Digital version 2. Available from: http: // www. ars. usda. gov / SP 2 UserFiles / Place / 12454900 / Gagne _ 2014 _ World _ Cecidomyiidae _ Catalog _ 3 r d _ Edition. pdf (Accessed 27 Jan. 2017)" type="journal article" year="2014">Gagné &amp; Jaschhof 2014</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D17FFC49FE44FC54" box="[339,457,977,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D17FFC49FE44FC54" box="[339,457,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">P. leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only one with regularly two palpal segments (
<figureCitation id="0FB61B949C17FFB8D409FC4AFBF0FC54" box="[1061,1149,977,1002]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1480,1502]" captionTargetBox="[167,1408,204,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[163,1425,195,1457]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – D. Peromyia leveillei, male (specimens from Sweden). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C: Palpus, lateral. D: Wing, dorsal. Scales for A – C, 0.05 mm, for D, 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265190/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
), all others have three or four. This specific character helped us to identify three 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D320FC6DFCF4FBB3" box="[780,889,1014,1037]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D320FC6DFCF4FBB3" box="[780,889,1014,1037]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males from southern 
<collectingCountry id="EF9A47819C17FFB8D45DFC6EFB47FBB0" box="[1137,1226,1013,1038]" name="Sweden" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Sweden</collectingCountry>
as belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D5ABFC6DFF7DFB8C" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D5ABFC6DFF7DFB8C" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">P. leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an identification verified by comparing with Kleesattel’s (1979) male genitalic illustration (fig. 30.72). The Swedish specimens, which represent the species’ rediscovery after more than 120 years, serve here to complete the male descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D234FBF9FD01FBC4" box="[536,652,1121,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D234FBF9FD01FBC4" box="[536,652,1121,1146]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">P. leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by previous authors.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DF97549A9C17FFB8D0EBFB1EFDEEF8B9" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="973207119C17FFB8D0EBFB1EFC0EFACB" blockId="7.[151,1437,761,2015]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D0EBFB1EFECCFB20" bold="true" box="[199,321,1157,1182]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The two-segmented palpus (
<figureCitation id="0FB61B949C17FFB8D2BAFB1EFD62FB20" box="[662,751,1157,1182]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1480,1502]" captionTargetBox="[167,1408,204,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[163,1425,195,1457]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – D. Peromyia leveillei, male (specimens from Sweden). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C: Palpus, lateral. D: Wing, dorsal. Scales for A – C, 0.05 mm, for D, 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265190/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D38DFB1DFBFCFB20" box="[929,1137,1157,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D38DFB1DFBFCFB20" box="[929,1137,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D505FB1DFA18FB23" box="[1321,1429,1158,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D505FB1DFA18FB23" box="[1321,1429,1158,1181]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D124FB31FE41FB7F" box="[264,460,1194,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororia" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D124FB31FE41FB7F" box="[264,460,1194,1217]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia sororia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BECA66789C17FFB8D1F8FB31FDCBFB7F" box="[468,582,1194,1217]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, a closely related species described below. 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D400FB31FB75FB7C" box="[1068,1272,1193,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D400FB31FB75FB7C" box="[1068,1272,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D502FB31FA16FB7F" box="[1326,1435,1194,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororia">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D502FB31FA16FB7F" box="[1326,1435,1194,1217]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">P. sororia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from the congeneric species by the roundish wings (
<figureCitation id="0FB61B949C17FFB8D319FB56FC1CFB58" box="[821,913,1229,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1480,1502]" captionTargetBox="[167,1408,204,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[163,1425,195,1457]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – D. Peromyia leveillei, male (specimens from Sweden). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C: Palpus, lateral. D: Wing, dorsal. Scales for A – C, 0.05 mm, for D, 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265190/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Both belong to the 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D4A9FB55FF55FAB4" authority="Felt, 1907" authorityName="Felt" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D4A9FB55FAD5FB58" box="[1157,1368,1229,1254]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Peromyia modesta</emphasis>
(Felt, 1907)
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D118FB6AFDEBFAB4" author="Jaschhof" box="[308,614,1265,1290]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2009) The Wood Midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae: Lestremiinae) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 18, 1 - 333." type="journal article" year="2009">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and there to a subset of species whose tegmen has no obvious ventral plate, including 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D17EFA8DFDEBFA90" authority="Jaschhof, 2001" authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="2001" box="[338,614,1301,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cassa">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D17EFA8DFE23FA93" box="[338,430,1302,1325]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">P. cassa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D194FA8EFDEBFA90" author="Jaschhof" box="[440,614,1301,1326]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Jaschhof, M. (2001) On the Lestremiinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Japan. Part 2: Tribe Peromyiini Kleesattel, 1979. Esakia, 41, 37 - 147." type="journal article" year="2001">Jaschhof, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D259FA8DFBA8FA90" authority="Mamaev &amp; Berest, 1994" authorityName="Mamaev &amp; Berest" authorityYear="1994" box="[629,1061,1302,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concitata">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D259FA8DFD71FA93" box="[629,764,1302,1325]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">P. concitata</emphasis>
Mamaev &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="F31C7AE09C17FFB8D3BEFA8DFBA8FA90" author="Berest" box="[914,1061,1302,1326]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" refString="Berest, Z. L. (1994) Gall midges of the tribe Peromyini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae): origins, contents, and a new classification approach. Vestnik Zoologii, 1994 (2), 20 - 27. [In Russian]" type="journal article" year="1994">Berest, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and two unnamed species from 
<collectingCountry id="EF9A47819C17FFB8D0BBFAA1FF7CFAEC" box="[151,241,1338,1362]" name="Norway" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Norway</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="EF9A47819C17FFB8D103FAA2FE09FAEC" box="[303,388,1337,1362]" name="Austria" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Austria</collectingCountry>
, respectively, in the Jaschhof collection. While the gonostyli of the latter four species are elongate, those of 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D148FAC5FE55FAC8" box="[356,472,1373,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leveillei">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D148FAC5FE55FAC8" box="[356,472,1373,1398]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">P. leveillei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="508D7C929C17FFB8D222FAC5FDF6FACB" box="[526,635,1374,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororia">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D222FAC5FDF6FACB" box="[526,635,1374,1397]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">P. sororia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are markedly compact.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="973207119C17FFB8D0EBFA1AFDEEF8B9" blockId="7.[151,1437,761,2015]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D0EBFA1AFE50FA24" bold="true" box="[199,477,1409,1434]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Other male characters.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="5075AAF49C17FFB8D25BFA19FC8FFA27" box="[631,770,1410,1434]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D322FA1AFCD9FA24" bold="true" box="[782,852,1409,1434]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Head.</emphasis>
Eye bridge 3–4 ommatidia long dorsally. Postfrons strongly projecting. Postocular bristles in 1 row. Neck and node of fourth flagellomere equally long, node with irregular whorl of long hair-shaped translucent sensilla distally, such sensilla present also medially, there shorter, intermingled with setae (
<figureCitation id="0FB61B949C17FFB8D197FA76FD9AF9B8" box="[443,535,1517,1542]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1480,1502]" captionTargetBox="[167,1408,204,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[163,1425,195,1457]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – D. Peromyia leveillei, male (specimens from Sweden). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C: Palpus, lateral. D: Wing, dorsal. Scales for A – C, 0.05 mm, for D, 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265190/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Both palpal segments with hair-shaped translucent sensilla, apical segment pointed, twice as long as basal segment (
<figureCitation id="0FB61B949C17FFB8D2A1F98AFD61F994" box="[653,748,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1480,1502]" captionTargetBox="[167,1408,204,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[163,1425,195,1457]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – D. Peromyia leveillei, male (specimens from Sweden). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C: Palpus, lateral. D: Wing, dorsal. Scales for A – C, 0.05 mm, for D, 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265190/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D32AF98AFCCAF994" bold="true" box="[774,839,1553,1578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="0FB61B949C17FFB8D371F98AFC33F994" box="[861,958,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1480,1502]" captionTargetBox="[167,1408,204,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[163,1425,195,1457]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – D. Peromyia leveillei, male (specimens from Sweden). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C: Palpus, lateral. D: Wing, dorsal. Scales for A – C, 0.05 mm, for D, 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265190/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Length / width 2.2. Most of venation conspicuously poor in contrast. Costal break indistinct. Strong anterior portion of C extends beyond R5 for 2–3 times the vein width. R1 = 1.5–2.0 Rs. M4/CuA-fork wide. 
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D374F9C7FC1AF9CB" bold="true" box="[856,919,1628,1653]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Legs.</emphasis>
Claws curved at right angle, without teeth, broadened subapically. 
<emphasis id="A5F9DB039C17FFB8D19EF918FDADF922" bold="true" box="[434,544,1667,1692]" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="0FB61B949C17FFB8D216F918FD10F925" box="[570,669,1667,1692]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1480,1502]" captionTargetBox="[167,1408,204,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[163,1425,195,1457]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – D. Peromyia leveillei, male (specimens from Sweden). A: Genitalia, ventral. B: Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C: Palpus, lateral. D: Wing, dorsal. Scales for A – C, 0.05 mm, for D, 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265190/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="553">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of ninth tergite blunt rather than rounded. Gonocoxites: ventral emargination deep, V-shaped, membranous basally; dorsal bridge slightly wider than tegmen. Gonostylus almost globular in ventral view, bent, concave medially. Tegmen three times longer than wide, parallelsided, rounded apically, apodemes small.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
